physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General - No acute distress (NAD); Heart - Regular rate and rhythm (RRR), no murmurs; Lungs - Clear to auscultation bilaterally (CTAB); Abdomen - Soft, positive tenderness to palpation (TTP) in right upper quadrant (RUQ) with no guarding or rebound, minimal TTP in right lower quadrant (RLQ), negative ___; Extremities - No edema.
